Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.28,0:02:00.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质完全不同于我们在地球上所遇到的任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter is unlike anything we have ever encountered on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.49,0:02:02.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每一秒钟有数十亿个奇异粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Billions of these strange particles...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.70,0:02:06.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,穿过它们所遇到的任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pass through everything they encounter each second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:08.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们具有巨大的影响力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are so massive in weight...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:12.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,具有影响星系的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they have the power to influence the galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:15.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们的形成和它们旋转的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how they form and howfast they spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.18,0:02:23.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质的无形之手无处不在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter"s invisible presence is everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.68,0:02:25.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是这样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or so it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.02,0:02:31.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学没有直接证明暗物质粒子的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science has not directly proven dark matter particles exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.19,0:02:34.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有许多怀疑但没有答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are many suspects, but no answers...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.52,0:02:38.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察你无法看到的东西谈何容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and observing something you can't see isn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:42.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它并不发光也并不吸收光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt doesn't emit light, and it doesn't absorb light.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:44.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它对光根本就无动于衷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt doesn't interact with light at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.62,0:02:48.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不仅不发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not only does it not shine...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:50.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而且你还无法隐约看到它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can't easily see it in obscuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.71,0:02:55.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而科学知道其证据的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the evidence is there. Science knows it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.38,0:02:57.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上的每一本教科书\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every textbook on the planet Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.59,0:03:01.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都说宇宙是原子和某些亚原子构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}says that the universe is made out of atoms...and some subatomic particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:05.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,啊!所有这些教科书都是错误的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, all those textbooks are wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.97,0:03:09.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们将去地底下给予证明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they are going underground to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:12.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当他们听说这个不可见的物质叫做暗物质时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When they hear about this invisible matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.06,0:03:15.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们说:"呸 胡说"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called dark matter, they say, "Bah, humbug."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:18.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拿出暗物质存在的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Show me proof that dark matter exists."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.03,0:03:26.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,明尼苏达州… 苏丹 远离大城市灯光200英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Soudan, Minnesota, 200 miles from any major city lights...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.78,0:03:29.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个搜寻暗物质的理想之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a perfect place for hunting dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.70,0:03:32.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是并非为了显而易见的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but not for obvious reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:35.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么你会认为我们想仰望星空来寻找暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you'd think we'd want to look up in the sky for dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:37.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里毕竟是暗物质来的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's where dark matter is coming from, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.42,0:03:39.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恰恰相反我们将带上头盔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But instead, we're going to don our helmets...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.05,0:03:40.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,深入到这个矿井的下面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we're going to walk down into this mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.51,0:03:51.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地下2431英尺的地方是苏丹国家实验室\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}2,431 feet underground is the Soudan National Laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.64,0:03:56.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个废弃的铁矿改造成了一个研究机构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an abandoned iron mine reconfigured into a research facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.94,0:03:59.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里只是全球许多实验室之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is just one lab of many around the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:04.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,放在地下是为了让实验免遭宇宙射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}going underground to shield experiments from cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.12,0:04:09.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每一个都在争相发现暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each are racing to detect dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.79,0:04:13.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种只能间接观察的无形粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an invisible particle that has only been indirectly observed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.67,0:04:15.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但从未捕获过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but never captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:20.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在这里已经有10年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've been at this for, now, a decade...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.63,0:04:22.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尚未看到过一个暗物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we have yet to see a dark matter particle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.09,0:04:28.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻暗物质始于近一个世纪前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hunt for dark matter started almost a century ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:33.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家终于有了深入夜空观察的工具\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers finally had the tools to see deep into the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:35.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,问题出现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the questions began.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:37.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直至1920年代后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it wasn't until the 1920s...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:40.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科技有了长足的发展\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the technology developed well enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.53,0:04:43.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,以致我们能够对这些模糊的小斑点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that we could take the little fuzzy patches...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:45.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们已经在望远镜里注意到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that people had noticed in their telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:47.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,进行分析并搞清楚它们是什么东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and resolve them and figure out what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.03,0:04:50.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当时埃德温·哈勃震惊了世界\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then, Edwin Hubble shocked the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.99,0:04:55.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宣称宇宙远不止银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and declared the universe was bigger thanjust the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.25,0:04:57.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们意识到这些模糊的小斑点中的某些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People realized that some of these little fuzzy patches...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.00,0:05:01.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是单个的星系 就像我们的银河系一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are separate galaxies, just like our Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.67,0:05:07.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在天文学家发现新的星系的同时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As astronomers discovered new galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,加州理工学院教授弗里茨·兹维基仰望\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cal Tech professor Fritz Zwicky looked up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:13.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,后发星系团周边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the neighboring Coma Cluster of galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.18,0:05:15.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察到了一些奇怪的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and observed something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.69,0:05:22.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在他测量后发星系团运动的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When he measured what the motions were...in the Coma Cluster of galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:26.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他得出了那个星团有多少质量的估计值\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he got an estimate for how much mass there was in that cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.15,0:05:28.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在他比较有多少质量时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then he compared it to how much mass...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.57,0:05:30.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你其实可以通过观察那些星系来看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could actually see by looking at the galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.45,0:05:34.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些东西并未增加\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something didn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:37.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系在星团里运动迅速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxies were moving too fast within the cluster...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:40.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相对他能看到的发光物质的数量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the amount of illuminated stuff he could see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.55,0:05:44.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过他的计算\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By his calculations...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.05,0:05:47.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里应该有发光物质160多倍的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there should have been 160 times more illuminated mass...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.88,0:05:51.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来解释星团里的星系的随机速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to account for the random speeds of galaxies in the cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.89,0:05:54.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有别的什么东西在影响着它们的运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something else was affecting their motions...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:55.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而是什么东东呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.98,0:05:59.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他分析了它们的运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He analyzed their motions...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.48,0:06:02.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,断定那个星团并不稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and concluded that the cluster could not be stable...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.69,0:06:05.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,除非有大量的暗物质存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unless there was a large amount of dark matter present.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.15,0:06:08.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1933年他是最早真正领悟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln 1933, he was one of the first people...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:11.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质存在意义的人之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to really grasp the significance...of the presence of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.57,0:06:13.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他称它为… 失踪的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He called it "missing matter."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.70,0:06:19.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质:一种无形的物质 具有万有引力的吸引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter, an invisible mass that was gravitationally attractive...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:25.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能够影响到星团里全部星系的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and was able to affect the speeds...of entire galaxies in a cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:26.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,革命性的思想？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Revolutionary thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.67,0:06:30.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对 但是这一发现很大程度被忽视了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yes, but the discovery was largely ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.81,0:06:36.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为人们把兹维基当真\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l think that people took Zwicky seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:38.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是他们不敢妄下结论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they didn'tjump to any conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:41.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那时宇宙才刚刚开始探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was a time when the universe...was just beginning to be explored.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:43.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到了1920年我们才认识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt was the 1920s when we first realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.61,0:06:45.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的星系以外还有星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there were galaxies outside our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.73,0:06:49.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们过去不知道它就是星系还是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we didn't know back then was whether it was simply galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:51.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星 气体 尘埃 我们无法看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or stars or gas or dust that we couldn't see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.99,0:06:53.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是不是什么完全不同的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or whether it was something truly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:07:01.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,兹维基的意见基于测量恒星和星系的质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Zwicky's observations were based on measuring the mass...in the stars and galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.79,0:07:04.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而你是如何称重空间的东西的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how do you weigh stuff in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:08.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你不可能将太阳放在天平上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can't go and put the Sun on a scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.76,0:07:09.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这有那么一点困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a little bit hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:11.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而你能做的就是你可以测量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what you can do is you can measure...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.63,0:07:14.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星围绕着太阳运转的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how fast the planets are moving around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:16.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳里的物质越多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the more stuff there is in the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.56,0:07:19.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些行星必定会在自己的轨道上运转得越快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the faster those planets have to move...to stay in their orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.81,0:07:23.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,牛顿和爱因斯坦都说过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton and Einstein both said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.40,0:07:26.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个物体中的质量或东西越多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more mass or stuff you have in an object...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:29.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其所具有的万有引力就越强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the more gravitational pull it will have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.82,0:07:33.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物体距离其中心越远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the further an object is from the center...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:36.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在轨运行就应该越慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the slower it should travel in orbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:39.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是因为万有引力较弱的缘故\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the gravitational pull is weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.87,0:07:43.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,根据爱因斯坦的广义相对论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to Einstein's general theory of relativity...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.67,0:07:46.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,乃至根据牛顿的万有引力理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or even according to Newtonian gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有这些星系都相互吸引着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of the galaxies are pulling on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.97,0:07:55.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像太阳影响着我们的太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's like the Sun's influence on our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.22,0:07:58.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳的质量拽拉水星要快于冥王星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mass of the Sun pulls Mercury faster than Pluto...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.02,0:08:02.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为水星的位置更靠近太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because Mercury is positioned closer to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:04.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样对于一个星系来说你可以预料到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Likewise for a galaxy, you would expect...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.73,0:08:06.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着你越来越远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as you got further and further away...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.69,0:08:10.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物体在其轨道上的的运动也就越来越慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}things are moving more and more slowly...to stay in their orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:12.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而兹维基并未观察到这个情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Zwicky didn't observe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.82,0:08:17.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样50年后的一个年轻科学家维拉·鲁宾也为观察到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neither did a young scientist named Vera Rubin fifty years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:22.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,她在观察类似银河系这样的星系的旋转曲线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She was observing the rotational curves...of galaxies similar to the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:28.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和兹维基一样她的意见同样看似怪异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like Zwicky, her observations also seemed strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:32.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,维拉·鲁宾实际测量到的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What Vera Rubin actually measured was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:34.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着你越来越远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as you got further and further away...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.22,0:08:37.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,旋转的气体和尘埃的速度始终如一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the velocity of the orbiting gas and dust remained constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:42.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,鲁宾观察到的就好象城市比作星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What Rubin observed was as if a citywere a galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.60,0:08:46.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,路上的每一辆汽车就是行星或恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and every car on the road was a planet or star.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.56,0:08:48.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管交通流量如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And despite the amount of traffic...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.77,0:08:52.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个城市里的每辆汽车的速度都是相同的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every car traveled around the city at the same speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:57.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种同样恒定的运转速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This same, consistent rotational speed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.11,0:09:00.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管物质的量 交通量如何\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}despite the amount of stuff, or traffic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.37,0:09:02.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是鲁宾世纪观察到的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was exactly what Rubin observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:07.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系的外围部分运转得够快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The outer parts of the galaxy were rotating fast enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.79,0:09:09.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,必定会有更多的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there must be a lot more mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.59,0:09:11.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,否则星系会飞散\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other wise, the galaxy would have flown apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.42,0:09:16.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,唯一解释这个星系快上10倍的悖论的途径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only way to resolve this paradox...of galaxies which spin ten times too fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:19.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是假设那里有一个光晕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is to assume that there is a halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.85,0:09:23.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个无形物质组成的光晕围绕着星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a halo of invisible matter surrounding the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:25.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,保持着星系的完整\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}keeping the galaxy whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.64,0:09:29.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质存在于星系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter was present in the galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:34.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它具有足够的质量来保持恒定的运转速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it had enough mass to keep the rotation speed constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.44,0:09:37.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把我想象成暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lmagine that l am the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.28,0:09:39.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个球之围绕着我的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This ball is a star orbiting me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.62,0:09:42.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我的引力一直将它保持在空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because my gravitational force is keeping it in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.95,0:09:44.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而即使你看不到我\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even if you couldn't see me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.66,0:09:46.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你也会知道这里必定有着什么东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would know there must be something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:49.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,否则恒星就会沿着一条直线飞离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Otherwise, the star would just zoom off in a straight line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.21,0:09:51.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,必定存在着产生引力的某种东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There must be something causing that gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:53.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是我们知道必定存在着暗物质的原因所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's how we know that there must be dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.71,0:10:00.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,鲁宾估计暗物质比普通的发光体多出10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rubin estimated that there was ten times more dark matter...han ordinary illuminated stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:06.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此后 我们分析了数百个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since then, we've analyzed hundreds of galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.14,0:10:08.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都是同样的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they all have the same pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.14,0:10:10.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都为了自身的利益旋转得非常快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They all rotate too fast for their own good...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.61,0:10:13.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都需要暗物质来抱成团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they need dark matter to hold them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:15.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这一次科学界重视了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This time, science paid attention...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:19.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,开始思索:暗物质是啥东西？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and started to wonder: What is dark matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.57,0:10:22.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你如何在太空中发现这无形的东西呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How do you find something that is invisible in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:29.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们需要找到暗物质在宇宙间藏身之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They needed to see just where dark matter...was hiding out in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:31.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,即使他们无法看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even if they couldn't see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.00,0:10:35.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学也已经认识到了暗物质通过弯曲经过的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}science realized that dark matter exposed itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.88,0:10:38.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自我暴露出来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by bending light that passes through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.34,0:10:44.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这叫做引力透镜 实际上是个聚光灯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's called gravitational lensing, and it's a virtual spotlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.22,0:10:48.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暴露了宇宙间所有的无形物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that uncovers any invisible stuff in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:51.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它的情况与所有的物质并无二异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What it does do is it does what all matter does...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:54.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它能够弯曲光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in that it can deflect the light ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:59.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以光线在传播过程中会被暗物质弯曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So a light ray can be deflected in its path by dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.95,0:11:02.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过追踪变形的光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By tracing the battered light's path...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.53,0:11:05.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现暗物质的引力透镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gravitational lensing detected dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.83,0:11:09.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,聚焦到了星系的光晕中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}concentrated in the halos of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:12.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力透镜证明是极其准确的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravitational lensing proved to be infallible...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:15.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质的存在突然被揭示了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dark matter's presence was suddenly revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.67,0:11:19.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种引力透镜的技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This technique of gravitational lensing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.63,0:11:22.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是最准确的 因为我们实际上能够准确描述\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the most precise because we can actually pinpoint...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:25.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不仅是有多少暗物质存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not just how much dark matter there is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.51,0:11:29.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而且它分布在空间的具体位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but how it's distributed in its position on the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:35.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为我们测量了光线经过暗物质的变形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's because we can measure the distortion...of the light rays passing through the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:38.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你是怎么知道你的眼镜的位置的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How do you know that your glasses are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.07,0:11:39.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为它折射了光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because it bends light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:40.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:43.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过观察哈勃的宇宙空间照片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by looking at Hubble space pictures of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:47.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察光线经过星系时的变形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and looking at the distortion of light...as it goes through galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.74,0:11:50.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就得到了暗物质的分布图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we actually have maps of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.71,0:11:54.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系的大部分质量来自暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the mass of a galaxy is from the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:59.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普通的物质聚集在暗物质的引力场里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ordinary matter accumulates...in the gravitational field of the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.84,0:12:03.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而一旦暗物质出现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But once dark matter came on the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:07.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家想知道 它究竟是一种新的未被侦检的粒子呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists wondered if it was a new, undetected particle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.35,0:12:10.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还只是无形的普通物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orjust invisible ordinary matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:12.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在人们发现暗物质时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When people found dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.02,0:12:15.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大家都想知道 那是什么东东 知道吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everybody wanted to know, well, what is it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.40,0:12:17.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然啦最早的答案是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, of course, the first answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:19.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它只是构建你我的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's just the stuff that makes up you and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.44,0:12:20.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是不发光而已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's not shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.69,0:12:27.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家开始调查不发光的宇宙间的对象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists started to investigate objects...in the universe that didn't emit light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.95,0:12:29.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,黑洞考虑到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Black holes were considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:33.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们不发光且能够将物质吸引过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They don't emit light, can draw matter to themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.46,0:12:36.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这已经通过引力透镜发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and are detected with gravitational lensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.92,0:12:38.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它的形式可能采用黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt could take a form of black holes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:41.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或者MACHOs 大质量天体物理密实晕体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or MACHOs, massive compact halo objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:44.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些基本上是昏暗的小恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are basically dark, small stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.80,0:12:46.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不会发出太多的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that don't give off a lot of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.26,0:12:49.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,MACHOs隐藏在银河系的光晕外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}MACHOs hide out in the halo of the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.01,0:12:53.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是通过引力透镜发现的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and are detected by gravitational lensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:57.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但够不上暗物质所需要的量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there weren't enough...to account for the amount of dark matter needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.82,0:13:03.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,褐矮星之类的衰败恒星也值得怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Failed stars like brown dwarfs were also suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.61,0:13:08.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们数量可观足以弥补暗物质的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are massive enough to make up dark matter's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.99,0:13:12.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管暗物质是什么 它超过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whatever dark matter is, there is way more of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:17.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,恒星和行星等普通物质10倍还多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the ordinary matter of stars and planets...ten times more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:24.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,构成普通的原子 质子 中子 电子的所有材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All the stuff that you can construct...from ordinary atoms, protons, and neutrons and electrons...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.72,0:13:30.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都不足以达到你所看到的星系和星团的物质总量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cannot possibly be enough...to account for the total amount of matter...that you see in galaxies and clusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:35.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家在继续搜寻暗物质的同时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists continued to present new suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.52,0:13:38.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不断提出新的嫌疑人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the search continued for dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.90,0:13:41.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,此前发现的奇异粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Previously discovered exotic particles...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:43.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如中微子就被重新考虑了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like neutrinos, were reconsidered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.24,0:13:48.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和暗物质一样中微子穿过地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like dark matter, neutrinos are passing through the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:51.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每秒钟数百万个粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}millions of particles at a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.28,0:13:52.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它们太轻了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they are too light...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.49,0:13:55.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,难以解释暗物质对引力的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to account for dark matter's effect on gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.66,0:14:00.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家可以在粒子对撞机里重现中微子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and scientists can recreate neutrinos in particle colliders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:02.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们同样来自太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They also come from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.63,0:14:07.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,轴子[Axions]是另一个潜在的暗物质粒子的候选者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Axions is also another possible dark matter candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.97,0:14:14.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们的发明是为了解释粒子物理理论中的一个特定的差错\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were invented to explain a particular glitch...in one of the particle physics theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.47,0:14:16.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们会是非常轻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They would be extremely light...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.48,0:14:18.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你搜寻它们要以一个完全不同的方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you search for them in a completely different way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:21.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相对我们在做的 但是会是…\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than what we're doing, but there would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.23,0:14:22.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们同样会是非常多的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They would also be very numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:25.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此它们有可能是暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so they could possibly be the dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.53,0:14:27.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,轴子非常轻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Axions are very light...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.15,0:14:32.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,被认为诞生于大爆炸那一刻就像暗物质一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and are believed to have been created...at the moment of the Big Bang, just like dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.87,0:14:36.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是理论上认为它们会变成质子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But theories suggest that they can change to protons...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.25,0:14:38.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而暗物质是稳定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while dark matter is stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.37,0:14:41.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在折腾了所有的一般嫌疑人后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After exhausting all the usual suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:46.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,许多科学家认为暗物质是一种新的奇异的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}many scientists believe dark matter is a new, exotic particle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.42,0:14:48.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不同于地球上的任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unlike anything on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:52.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每秒钟有数十亿个穿过我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and billions are passing through us every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.18,0:14:58.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在发现暗物质之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up until the discovery of dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.06,0:15:00.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家一直认为宇宙的构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists believed the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.06,0:15:04.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是质子 中子 电子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was made only of protons, neutrons, and electrons...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.06,0:15:06.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些构成地球的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the stuff everything on Earth is made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.07,0:15:09.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道还有一些物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we know it has some mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.95,0:15:13.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们还有一些尚未被发现的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're left with something that we've not yet detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:16.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而对于理想的暗物质候选者来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But to be a perfect dark matter candidate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.91,0:15:19.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它必须具有某些物理属性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it must have certain physical properties...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:22.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普通的嫌疑人都配不上这样的罪行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and none of the usual suspects were fitting the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.79,0:15:27.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们知道暗物质是某种笨重的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we know the dark matter is some ponderous substance...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.42,0:15:29.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道它运动得并不太快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we know that it's not moving too quickly...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.38,0:15:30.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道我们无法看见它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we know that we can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.72,0:15:34.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质粒子并不以光速移动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter particles are not traveling at the speed of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.26,0:15:37.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们并不会对你我或其它所有的东西产生影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they don't interact with you and me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.81,0:15:42.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是为什么非常难以捕捉到这些粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or anything prettywell, and that's why it's been so difficult...to track down these particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.65,0:15:44.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它并不会对普通物质产生影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it doesn't interact with ordinary matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.56,0:15:46.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,除了引力之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}except through gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:48.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我手里有些暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf l had some dark matter in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:49.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它是具有分量的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would have weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.65,0:15:52.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是首先它会在我的指缝间消散掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But first it would dissolve right through my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.82,0:15:57.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们所谓的标准模型粒子物理学里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There aren't any candidates for cold dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:15:59.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于冷暗物质并没有任何嫌疑对象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}within what we call the standard model particle physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.08,0:16:05.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和隐形人穿墙一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like an invisible man passing through walls...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.04,0:16:09.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每秒钟有数十亿个暗物质穿过地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark matter is passing through Earth billions of particles at a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.42,0:16:11.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从来没有碰撞到普通物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}never colliding with ordinary matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:17.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以对于暗物质是什么的最普遍的概念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the most popular idea for what the dark matter could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:18.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是叫做WIMP的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is something called a WlMP.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.06,0:16:22.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,WIMP就是弱相互作用重粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}WlMPs are weakly interacting massive particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.60,0:16:25.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们从未被发现过 但是它们的特性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have not been detected, but their characteristics...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:27.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,匹配理想的暗物质嫌疑人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}match the perfect dark matter candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.44,0:16:32.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在苏丹实验室里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the Soudan Laboratory...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:35.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室研究小组已经来到了地下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Fermilab team has gone underground,,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.53,0:16:37.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,勇敢面对数以千计的蝙蝠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}braving thousands of bats...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.95,0:16:40.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,试图捕获到WIMP粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to try and capture a WlMP particle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:44.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是所谓的低温暗物质搜寻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is called the cryogenic dark matter search.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:46.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,CDMS是其简称\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}CDMS is the acronym for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.71,0:16:52.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里过去是个铁矿 直到1962年才被关闭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was an iron ore mine until 1962 when it shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.51,0:16:54.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在地下半英里处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're half a mile underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:58.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室设计了一台机器 在零度以下的温度中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fermilab has designed a machine that, at subzero temperatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.80,0:17:02.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以检测经过其中的暗物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can detect a dark matter particle passing through it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.02,0:17:05.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它的传感器用的材料是锗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its sensor is made of germanium...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.31,0:17:08.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种挤满原子的高密度金属\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a dense metal jam-packed with atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.65,0:17:11.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是块高纯锗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a very pure block of germanium.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.86,0:17:14.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在其表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's got on the surface of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.53,0:17:17.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,装有微小的温度计 基本上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a pattern of tiny little thermometers, basically...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.74,0:17:25.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能够发现粒子穿过这个曲棍球大小的锗块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are able to detect when a particle passes...through this hockey puck-sized chunk of germanium.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.08,0:17:27.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质现在正流过我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter is streaming right through us right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:28.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,没有任何动静\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.96,0:17:33.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,极其偶然时它会撞上一个原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Very occasionally, it will bump into the nucleus of an atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.42,0:17:36.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是我们希望看到的签名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's the signature that we're hoping to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.26,0:17:39.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为了得到一个清晰的暗物质撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To get a clean dark matter hit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.34,0:17:42.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室需要过滤掉空间的垃圾\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fermilab needed to filter out junk from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.93,0:17:45.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会得到非常多的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would get so many particles...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.64,0:17:49.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这真的是在大海里捞针\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it would be really trying to sift a needle in a haystack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.94,0:17:52.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室的实验收集\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fermilab's experiment picks up all matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.94,0:17:54.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有经过这个探测器的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that passes through this detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.49,0:17:56.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,空气中的垃圾越少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lessjunk in the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:18:00.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现暗物质粒子就越容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the easier it will be to detect a dark matter particle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:08.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为暗物质不易对正常的质子和电子产生影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because dark matter doesn't interact easily...with regular protons and electrons...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.79,0:18:11.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室已经冷冻了锗块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fermilab has frozen the germanium pucks...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:13.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温度接近了零下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to near subzero temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.84,0:18:17.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果暗物质粒子穿过并击中了原子核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf a dark matter particle comes through and hits a nucleus...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:22.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么实际上会极细微地改变结晶体的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will actually change the temperature of the crystal very slightly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:26.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么我们观察结晶体温度的细微变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so we're looking for that tiny change...of temperature in the crystal...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:29.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那是暗物质粒子经过的信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to signal that a dark matter particle has passed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:34.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,16个锗块安放在一个洁净室里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sixteen germanium pucks...sit in a chamber inside a clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.32,0:18:36.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们穿好了工作服\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we're suited up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:38.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将要进入实验室了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're about to go into the experimental room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.82,0:18:40.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个一万级的洁净室\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a Class 10,000 clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.53,0:18:43.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是我们都要穿上工作服的原因 我们不能带进任何尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's whywe're all suited up so we don't carry in any dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.28,0:18:45.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为会影响的实验的环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because that would cause background for the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.66,0:18:46.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,进去吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So let's go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.46,0:18:53.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里有闪烁计数器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we have scintillation counters...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.29,0:18:58.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,正在捕捉任何到达这地下的宇宙射线的粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are catching any cosmic-ray particles...that get all the way down underground here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.01,0:19:02.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这 保持着我们实验的低温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So right here is what keeps our experiment cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:03.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比绝对零度稍高一点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a tiny little bit above absolute zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.01,0:19:05.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这是稀释制冷机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the dilution refrigerator.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.02,0:19:10.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里面就是锗硅探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So way inside here...are the germanium and silicon detectors...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.27,0:19:14.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们就等着WIMP暗物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we're just waiting for a WlMP, a dark matter particle...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.65,0:19:16.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来到这深处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to get down to this depth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.48,0:19:20.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,撞击隐藏在保护罩里的这些锗硅结晶体中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and hit one of those germanium and silicon crystals...that's buried way inside all the shields.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:25.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室在近两年里一直在光顾这座矿井\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fermilab has been visiting the mine for nearly two years...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.37,0:19:27.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,试图捕捉到暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trying to capture dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:31.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这谈何容易\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is far harder than it sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.42,0:19:35.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管一次会有数十亿个粒子穿过地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although billions of particles are passing through Earth at one time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:37.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是百万分之一的概率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's a one-in-a-million shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.25,0:19:40.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质会和普通物质发生作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark matter will interact with ordinary matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.34,0:19:45.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让一个暗物质粒子撞击一个锗原子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Getting a dark matter particle to hit a germanium atom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:54.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,无异于弓箭手射中一英里开外的靶子的靶心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is like an archer trying to hit a bull's eye...when the target is a mile away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.48,0:19:57.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有这些绿灯指示出粒子在经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All these green lights indicate particles...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.40,0:20:01.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在楼下看到的锗硅探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}passing through the germanium and silicon detectors...that we saw downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.07,0:20:04.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些几乎无疑是背景粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are almost certainly all background particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:07.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而或许隐藏在里面某个地方就是WIMP\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But maybe it's buried in there someplace as a WlMP...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:09.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是我们无从知晓 直到我们分析了数据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we won't know until we analyze the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.08,0:20:12.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻暗物质枯燥乏味\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hunting dark matter is tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.29,0:20:16.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,费米实验室研究小组每天会去地下实验室报到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each day, the Fermilab team reports to the underground lab...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.34,0:20:20.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,分析数据 提高乒乓球水平\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}analyzes data, and perfects their ping-pong game...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.30,0:20:24.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同时等着一次证明暗物质存在的撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while waiting for the one hit that will prove dark matter exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.85,0:20:30.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而对于所有的努力和等待\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for all this effort and waiting around...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.14,0:20:35.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还没有暗物质被费米实验室以及其他人发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no dark matter has been detected by Fermilab or by anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.06,0:20:40.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,遗憾的是 迄今为止我们没有看到任何暗物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately, we've seen...precisely zero dark matter particles so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.28,0:20:47.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在任何时候我们都可能宣布\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Any day now, we may have the announcement...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:50.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物理学家已经在瓶子里捕捉到了暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that physicists have captured dark matter in a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.54,0:20:53.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们有一个假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.66,0:20:56.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,似乎无疑能够解释我们所在的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt certainly seems to explain the universe we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.96,0:20:58.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是明摆的事实就是我们尚未发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the plain fact is we haven't yet detected...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:00.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种冷暗物质粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this cold dark matter particle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:06.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,找到暗物质将不仅给我们证明了它的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding dark matter will not only give us proof of its existence...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.09,0:21:09.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而且也回答了空间的其它大问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but might also answer the other big questions of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.06,0:21:13.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发现暗物质将直接\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Detecting dark matter directly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:16.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为我们提供一个窗口 进入到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will give us a window onto what was going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.85,0:21:19.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大爆炸后的万分之一秒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}1/10,000th of a second after the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.73,0:21:25.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果科学家能够发现暗物质是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf scientists can discover what dark matter is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.20,0:21:29.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么他们也就有可能发现宇宙子其早期的情况了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they might also discover how the universe behaved early in its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.20,0:21:34.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质不仅是宇宙间的一个神秘的量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark matter is not only a mysterious quantity in the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.00,0:21:38.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你要明白同时那也是必须要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but also it's fundamental to our, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.33,0:21:39.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们出现在这的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why we're here, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.50,0:21:41.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,难以理解 形成星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt would be difficult to form galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.80,0:21:44.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从而 太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, hence, you know, the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.26,0:21:45.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从而 地球上的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, hence, life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.05,0:21:53.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质和暗能量的故事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The story of dark matter and dark energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.81,0:21:58.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是说不清楚的 如果不回到时间的起点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can't be told without going back to the beginning of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.35,0:22:03.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不回到当时不存在空间的大爆炸的那个瞬间的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the moment of the Big Bang when space didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.57,0:22:06.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不存在你能指出的中心位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was no center where you can point to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.03,0:22:09.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是大爆炸的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's exactly the analogy for the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:11.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在空中漫无方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There was no direction in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.07,0:22:14.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从那开始所有的星系都在不断地膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from which all the galaxies were expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.37,0:22:19.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从一无所有到剧烈地爆炸那一刻开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From this moment of nothing to a violent explosion...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.04,0:22:24.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,空间创造了 宇宙开始从一个种子成长起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}space was created, and the universe began to grow from a seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.88,0:22:30.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,粒子形成于气体和能量的核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Particles formed in a nuclearfusion of gas and energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.64,0:22:35.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普通物质与其它普通物质发生作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ordinary matter was reacting with other ordinary matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:38.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,早期的宇宙在诞生后1分钟时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The early universe was in fact a nuclear reactor...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.48,0:22:39.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实际上是一座核反应堆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was one minute old.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:46.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,38万年后粒子开始聚集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And 380,000 years later, bits of particles began to cluster...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.90,0:22:51.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,形成了后来形成恒星以及星系的种子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creating the seeds from which stars and galaxies would laterform.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.95,0:22:54.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,较大的团慢慢形成更大的团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bigger lumps grow to form yet bigger lumps...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.41,0:22:56.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此引力正缓慢地施加力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so gravity is a slowly pulling force...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.91,0:22:58.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将物体拉在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bringing objects together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.08,0:23:05.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家现在认识到了在大爆炸的瞬间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What scientists now realize was that at the moment of the Big Bang...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.84,0:23:07.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质也创造出来了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark matter was created.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.51,0:23:13.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它在帮助普通物质结合起来形成恒星与行星中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it played a critical role in helping ordinary matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.39,0:23:17.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,发挥了关键的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}clump together to form stars and planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:22.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像钢梁用于建筑工地一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like steel girders used on a building site...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.90,0:23:26.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质缓慢移动的粒子的作用就像是鹰架\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dark matter's slow-moving particles acted like scaffolding...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.03,0:23:30.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普通物质就可以自己依附上去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}upon which ordinary matter could attach itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.70,0:23:36.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们认为那是因为它温度很低不会有太多的影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We believe that, because it's cold and doesn't interact very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.49,0:23:39.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗物质靠引力结合在一块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that dark matter was pulled together by gravity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.96,0:23:44.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个过程非常缓慢地形成种子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very slowly over time...and actually formed the seeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.17,0:23:47.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,普通物质围绕着种子结合起来形成了星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}around which normal matter coalesced into galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.55,0:23:50.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就像是宇宙网 就像是蜘蛛网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's like a cosmic web, like a spider's web...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.55,0:23:52.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里存在着暗物质的丝线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where there are strands of dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.00,0:23:58.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些丝线相互交叉 就像鹰架的模样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and where these strands intersect, like a scaffolding pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.14,0:24:00.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以在这里 暗物质就是构架\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So in a sense, the dark matter is the framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.77,0:24:05.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它为我们能看到的闪亮的星系提供了构架\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's providing the scaffolding...for the shining galaxies that we can easily see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.65,0:24:08.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系其实就像圣诞树上的灯泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are really like the Christmas tree lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.73,0:24:10.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而不是真正的圣诞树\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're not the actual Christmas tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.53,0:24:13.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们是非常遥远都看得见的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're the things that are visible from very, very far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.82,0:24:17.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而真实的星系是一个大光晕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the reality of the galaxy is a big halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:18.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其中的大部分你是看不见的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}most of which you don't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.95,0:24:21.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你所看到的这些发光的点是恒星与行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You see the shiny bits that are stars and planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:24.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都堆积在那个大光晕的中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that have accumulated at the center of that large halo...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.17,0:24:25.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光晕的大部分是暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is mostly dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.00,0:24:30.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家长期以来困惑于为什么星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have long wondered why galaxies formed...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.17,0:24:33.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会形成看似在空间中随意分布的格局\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in seemingly random patterns across space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.34,0:24:39.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,现在科学家知道了那是因为暗物质的引力的作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now scientists know it's because of dark matter's gravitational pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.76,0:24:43.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙根本不是均匀的而是有空隙的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is not uniform at all, but has voids.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.52,0:24:46.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它有扎堆 有似乎有泡沫状的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has clumps, it seems to have bubble-like regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.52,0:24:50.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个 我们现在认为那是由于暗物质的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, we now believe it's due to dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.61,0:24:58.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,去年 天文学家已经能够将自己的理论更推进了一步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the last year, astronomers have been able...to take their theory one step further...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.24,0:25:00.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,利用引力透镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and create a detailed 3-D map...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.87,0:25:05.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,创造出了一个详细的宇宙间暗物质的3D分布图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of dark matter in the universe, using gravitational lensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.25,0:25:09.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦称引力影响万物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Einstein said that gravity affects everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.29,0:25:11.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像引力是由万物引起的一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like gravity is caused by everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.59,0:25:15.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,受引力影响的物体之一就是光本身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So one of the things that is affected by gravity is light itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.68,0:25:18.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为光经过暗物质 会弯曲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because when light goes through dark matter, it bends...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.68,0:25:21.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像光经过眼镜时受到弯曲那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just the way light bends when it goes through glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.89,0:25:26.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光不会区别对待普通物质和暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And light doesn't discriminate between ordinary matter and dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.31,0:25:31.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两种物质在光穿越星系时 都会改变它的路径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Both types of matter batter light's path as it travels through galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.99,0:25:36.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就像在地图上绘制航线一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like plotting a course on a map...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.20,0:25:41.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家追踪了数以千计的穿越暗物质的光源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers have traced thousands of light sources...as they pass through dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.41,0:25:45.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这给了科学最精准的图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has given science the most accurate picture yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.62,0:25:47.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,指出了暗物质在空间里的藏身之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of where dark matter hides in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.75,0:25:54.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以比较暗物质与星系的分布图\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can compare that map of the dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.76,0:25:57.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你瞧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with where the galaxies are, and, lo and behold...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.34,0:26:01.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们发现暗物质正充当着骨架\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we find that the dark matter is acting as the skeleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.26,0:26:05.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是围绕着这骨架 有形的物质聚集起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is the backbone around which the visible material is clumping.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.60,0:26:12.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过绘制宇宙的地图天文学家也能够回头去看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By mapping the universe, astronomers can also look back in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.07,0:26:15.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,预测在大爆炸时究竟创造出了多少物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and predict how much matter was created at the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.11,0:26:20.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你知道了宇宙现在显示出来的块头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So ifyou know how lumpy the universe appears now...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.45,0:26:22.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当年它在现在一半大的时候的块头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when it was half its current size...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.24,0:26:24.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有更早时的块头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and when it was half its current size before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.91,0:26:27.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么你就可以推断出宇宙中的物质总量了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can infer the total amount of stuff in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.75,0:26:30.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就给了我们一个非常好的匹配方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt gives us another very nice way of matching on...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.96,0:26:33.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们认为那就是暗物质的总量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to what we believe is the total amount of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.25,0:26:36.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们估计暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's estimated dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:39.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,占到宇宙的23%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}makes up twenty-three percent of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.09,0:26:42.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而普通物质只占4%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while ordinary matter makes up only four percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.93,0:26:45.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你需要大量的暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You need a lot of dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.02,0:26:49.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来解释这些星团和星系中所存在的引力的总量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to account for the total amount of gravity...that exists in these clusters and galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.98,0:26:55.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 占到宇宙最后73%的究竟是什么呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what makes up the final seventy-three percent of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.48,0:26:58.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家惊讶地发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists were shocked to discover...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.82,0:27:03.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一种神秘的暗能量正主宰着空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a new mysterious dark energy was dominating space.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.99,0:27:08.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其排斥能正将星系拉开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And its repulsive energy is driving the galaxies apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.92,0:27:16.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学一贯假设\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science always assumed...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.76,0:27:20.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管宇宙在不断地增大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that although the universe continues to grow in size...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.05,0:27:23.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是它终究会放慢膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would eventually slow in its expansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.09,0:27:25.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至有可能自我塌缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or perhaps even collapse on itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.68,0:27:29.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,引力会战胜它具有的所有的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity would overcome any momentum it had.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.19,0:27:34.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是在测量宇宙的膨胀史时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But while measuring the expansion history of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.52,0:27:37.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家惊讶地意识到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists were shocked to realize...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.15,0:27:39.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙并未慢下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the universe wasn't slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.65,0:27:40.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它还在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt was speeding up...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.86,0:27:45.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,严酷的命运等待着所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a grim fate awaited any living thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.78,0:27:47.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙会分裂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe will disintegrate...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.58,0:27:49.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,温度会变得非常的低\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and temperatures will become so cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.66,0:27:53.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,任何智能生命都将冻死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that any intelligent life will freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.38,0:27:58.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从大爆炸创造出了宇宙的那一刻开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the moment the Big Bang created the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.55,0:28:02.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,空间就一直在膨胀 从未停下脚步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}space has been expanding and never stopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.13,0:28:05.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,带着星系一路前进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}carrying galaxies along for the ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.43,0:28:09.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系间的空间正在膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The space in between the galaxies is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.06,0:28:11.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系却没有膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxies are not expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.52,0:28:12.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球没有膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is not expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.73,0:28:14.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,太阳系没有膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The solar system is not expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.31,0:28:17.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,哈勃在1929年第一个发现了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Edwin Hubble first discovered...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.07,0:28:21.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系在远离银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}galaxies were moving away from the Milky Way in 1929...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.44,0:28:24.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,基于了解到较为遥远的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by realizing the more distant galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.11,0:28:27.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,远离我们的速度比较近的星系来得快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}move faster away from us than the nearby ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.58,0:28:31.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他意识到自己可以通过研究它们经过菱镜的波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He realized he could measure theirvelocities...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.37,0:28:34.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来测量它们的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by studying their wavelengths through a prism.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.75,0:28:37.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就是所谓的测量红移\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's called measuring the red shift...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.09,0:28:40.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它还被用于测量空间的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is still used to measure distances in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.38,0:28:43.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他发现事实上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he found that, in fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.26,0:28:47.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系的距离越远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the greater the distance of a galaxy right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.51,0:28:49.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们离开我们的速度就越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the greater the speed with which it's moving away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.97,0:28:51.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,换句话就是红移越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is, the greater its red shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.68,0:28:54.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A few years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.06,0:28:57.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家决定用红移测量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers decided to use red shift measurements...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.15,0:28:59.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来测定宇宙的膨胀史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to measure the expansion history of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.57,0:29:03.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是你如何去测量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how do you measure...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.61,0:29:06.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙的整个膨胀史呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the entire expansion history of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.99,0:29:11.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你如何回到120亿年前呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How do you travel back twelve billion years in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.17,0:29:18.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们具有追溯时间的能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have the capability of going back in time directly...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.46,0:29:20.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,直接观察过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to observe the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.46,0:29:23.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个 和地质学家同样的手段 要知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, much in the same way as a geologist, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.92,0:29:25.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,观察大峡谷的岩层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looks at layers in the Grand Canyon...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.68,0:29:28.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着他记录下往下一层又一层的岩层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as he goes down into lower and lower layers...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.47,0:29:30.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就看到了历史的过去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looking back in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.51,0:29:34.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你看到更为遥远的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfyou look at progressively more distant galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.14,0:29:38.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你就看到了它们在更早时期的模样了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're looking at them as theywere...at progressively greater times in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.65,0:29:44.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为了测量膨胀的历史 科学家利用1A类超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To measure expansion history, scientists used Type 1a supernovas...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.57,0:29:46.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,作为他们的标准烛光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as their standard candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.74,0:29:52.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,举个例子 标准烛光可能就是一个100瓦的灯泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One example of a standard candle might be a100-watt light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.99,0:29:54.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以将灯泡这样的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You could have a bunch of these things...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.25,0:29:57.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,安放在房间四处与你不同距离的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sitting around in your room at different distances from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.67,0:30:01.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是较远的就会显得较昏暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then the more distant ones will appear fainter...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.63,0:30:04.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,较近的就会显得较亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the more nearby ones will appear brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.67,0:30:08.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1A类超新星始终恒定地发光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Type1a supernovas are always consistently brilliant...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.68,0:30:11.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,无论它们身处太空的何处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter where they occur in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.89,0:30:18.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,超新星恒星在其生命终结时急剧的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova is the colossal explosion of a star...at the end of its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.56,0:30:20.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是一声巨响!\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt just goes kabam.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.98,0:30:28.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当它成为一颗垂死的恒星时 所谓的白矮星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it occurs when a dying star, known as a white dwarf...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:30.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,经历了核心的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}goes through a nuclear runaway...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.03,0:30:33.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,把其自身喷发成碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and just literally blows itself to smithereens.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.91,0:30:38.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们发现1A类超新星在非常遥远的星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We find the Type 1a supernovae in very distant galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.87,0:30:40.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以看上去很昏暗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so they look really faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.38,0:30:43.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是我们将它们与较近的星系里的1A类超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then we compare them with Type1a supernovae...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.46,0:30:46.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相比较它们的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in nearby galaxies whose distance were...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.80,0:30:48.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,距离的测量是利用造父变星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Distances were measured using Cepheid variables...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.97,0:30:50.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或其它一些技巧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or some other technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.89,0:30:54.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,利用这些1A类超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using these Type 1a supernovas...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.60,0:30:57.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,1990年代分别有两个研究小组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}two different teams set out in the 1990s...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.77,0:31:00.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来测量宇宙的减速速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to measure the deceleration rate of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.81,0:31:04.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而为了在超新星出现是捕捉到它们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But to capture supernovas as they occur...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.77,0:31:08.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天文学家必须紧盯宇宙不放\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astronomers had to put the universe on surveillance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.28,0:31:13.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以将这个比作赌场监视\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can compare this a little bit to perhaps surveying a casino.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:16.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有的探头全程打开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So all these cameras are on all the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.16,0:31:19.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大部分时间里它们不会发现很多的有趣事情的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and most of the time, they don't find much of anything interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.54,0:31:22.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是偶 它们会发现要观察的东西的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, occasionally, they find what they're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.30,0:31:28.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须要观察大量的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have to look at lots of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.51,0:31:31.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们做的就是用上大望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what we did is we took large telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.26,0:31:34.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,装上广角相机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with cameras that have wide fields ofview...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.43,0:31:37.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所谓的广角就是满月的宽度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about as wide as, say, the width of the full Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.93,0:31:44.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会利用这个广角相机拍上许多太空的快照\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we took many snapshots of space using this wide-field camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.11,0:31:48.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,每张快照包括了数万个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And each snapshot contains tens of thousands of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.07,0:31:54.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过将遥远的1A类超新星的亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And by comparing the apparent brightness of the distant Type 1a's...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.24,0:31:59.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对比较近的星系里的1A类超新星的亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with those of the nearby Type 1a's in nearby galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.12,0:32:02.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就能够得出遥远星系的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can get the distance of the distant galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.62,0:32:04.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着时间的积累\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, hence, the amount of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.00,0:32:07.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就回顾了宇宙的历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we're looking back in the history of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.18,0:32:18.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在两个小组得到了60个1A类超新星的研究结果后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After the two teams studied the results...of sixty Type 1a supernovas...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.35,0:32:21.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家被他们的结果震惊了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}scientists were shocked at their results.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.85,0:32:24.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙并没有放慢脚步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe wasn't slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.48,0:32:26.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其膨胀还在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lts expansion was speeding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.32,0:32:31.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们都预计膨胀随着时间的推移在减缓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We all expected that expansion to be slowing down with time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.03,0:32:35.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 毕竟所有的星系在相互吸引\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because, after all, all of the galaxies are pulling on one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.66,0:32:40.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们非常肯定我们将测量到宇宙放慢的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We were so confident we were going to measure the rate...at which the universe was slowing down...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.29,0:32:42.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然我们发现的却是相反的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then we found, of course, a negative answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.66,0:32:44.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙并没有放慢脚步\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is not slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.12,0:32:45.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's speeding up...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.83,0:32:48.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这真是个大谜团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this was just a big mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.21,0:32:50.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这真的是非常怪异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is really, really weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.01,0:32:54.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道 我们曾预计测量到一定程度的减缓\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You know, we expected to measure some amount of slowdown...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.72,0:32:57.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相反 它的膨胀越发加快了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and instead, it's expanding more quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.22,0:32:59.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就像是个错误的信号对吧？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's like the wrong sign, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.39,0:33:00.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们真的很担心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We were really afraid...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.52,0:33:03.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们得到的是完全错误的答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we had gotten completely the wrong answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.77,0:33:06.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们再次检查了我们的测量成果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We rechecked our measurements.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.94,0:33:08.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们检查了分析报告\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We checked the analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.31,0:33:10.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,两个小组各自都有一帮人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A bunch of people on each of the two teams...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.69,0:33:13.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,进行测量 独立分析\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}did the measurements and the analysis independently...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.86,0:33:16.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不断得出同样的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and kept getting the same result.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.66,0:33:20.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙学界最近几年里最大的冲击之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the greatest shocks in the world of cosmology...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.95,0:33:26.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,已经认识到了我们的宇宙在加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just in the last few years has been the realization...that our universe is accelerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.50,0:33:29.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个驱动宇宙的排斥力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This repulsive force driving the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.67,0:33:33.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,叫做暗能量 一种无形的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was called dark energy, an invisible energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.05,0:33:36.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,谁都没有料到的 无法理解的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was nothing anyone expected or understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.01,0:33:42.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它表明在宇宙的最大距离范围内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt suggests that over the largest distances in the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.14,0:33:45.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,存在着一种排斥力 超过了引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's a repulsive effect that dominates over gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.94,0:33:49.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量在创造空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And dark energy was creating space...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.19,0:33:51.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,拉着星系一路往前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taking galaxies along for the ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.98,0:33:54.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种始终充满了宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This energy that appears to fill the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.65,0:33:56.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,延展宇宙膨胀越来越快的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and stretch the expansion of the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.86,0:34:02.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是现在所谓的暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}faster and faster with time is now known as dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.74,0:34:05.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这里我要扔出一个苹果 它开始减速了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So here l throw the apple, and, initially, it's decelerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.83,0:34:09.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而暗能量会把它加速远离我\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then dark energy makes it accelerate away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.33,0:34:10.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你扔出苹果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you throw the apple...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.79,0:34:14.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它就会飞离 一路加快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it just zooms away faster and faster with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.30,0:34:17.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,和苹果一路飞进太空一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like the apple forever traveling into space...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.47,0:34:28.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系被一路带到了创造出来的更大的空间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}galaxies are being carried away as more space is created.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.60,0:34:30.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你能想象一下的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So ifyou could imagine, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.35,0:34:33.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,教室里摆着椅子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a classroom populated by chairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.07,0:34:39.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那些椅子在教室里正慢慢地相互分开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and those chairs are slowly getting further apart...from one another within a classroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.78,0:34:44.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 要是所有的椅子像膨胀的宇宙一样延展开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because if all the chairs are being stretched apart...like in the expanding universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.54,0:34:46.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不论你坐在那把椅子上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter which chair you sit on...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.12,0:34:48.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你都会发现所有的椅子都在远离你\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you will find all chairs are moving away from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.96,0:34:51.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以椅子并没有真的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the chairs are not really expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.08,0:34:53.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 椅子的大小确实没有变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, the chairs are all the same size, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.54,0:34:56.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,结果是房间变得越来越大了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's happening is that the room is getting bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.21,0:34:59.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,椅子之间的空间变得越来越开了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the sort of the space in between the chairs...is being stretched apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.64,0:35:04.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,星系间正在创造出更大的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}More space is being created in between the galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.51,0:35:07.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 你看到单个的星系在宇宙中保持着固定的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you have individual galaxies remaining a constant size...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.81,0:35:11.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,整个空间变得越来越大了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a universe where all of space is getting bigger and bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.98,0:35:16.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量完全不同于暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy is very different from dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.86,0:35:21.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它不会像星团里的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt doesn't clump up like galaxies do in clusters...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.91,0:35:24.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或星系里的恒星那样抱团\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or like stars do in galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.53,0:35:26.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相反它表现出相当的均匀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lnstead, it appears to be pretty uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.70,0:35:29.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们发现等量的加速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we find the same amount of acceleration...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.16,0:35:31.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,无论我们往哪个方向看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}no matter which direction we look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.33,0:35:32.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它或许很平滑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's probably smooth...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.63,0:35:38.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管 有些人认为在其分布和影响中有可能存在纹理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}although some people believe there may be structure...in its distribution and its influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.17,0:35:40.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量是虚无的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy is the energy of the vacuum...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.01,0:35:42.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看不见 摸不着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the energy of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.26,0:35:44.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,虚无缥缈之中具有能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even nothingness has energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.55,0:35:48.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它将星系推开 创造失控的宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's pushing the galaxies apart, creating a runaway universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.93,0:35:52.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看来暗能量和暗物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt appears dark energy and dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.31,0:35:56.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,自时间开创以来就一直在相互竞争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have been at war with one another since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.65,0:35:59.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,科学家认为在大爆炸的那一刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science believes dark energy was created...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.19,0:36:03.03,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量与暗物质一道诞生了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along with dark matter at the moment of the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.07,0:36:05.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它一直存在于宇宙间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt has always existed in the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.66,0:36:09.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是暗物质的引力保持着对它的控制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but gravitational forces of dark matter kept it in check...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.87,0:36:12.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在最早的90亿年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slowing down the expansion of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.21,0:36:14.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,减缓了空间的膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during the first nine billion years of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.00,0:36:18.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这在50亿年前变化了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This changed five billion years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.67,0:36:20.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当时宇宙已经成长得够大了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the universe grew big enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.72,0:36:24.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以暗物质分布遍及整个宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that dark matter was dispersed throughout the universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.39,0:36:28.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量已经不再受到暗物质引力的影响了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dark energy wasn't so affected by dark matter's pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.56,0:36:33.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,结果宇宙开始加速膨胀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a result, the universe began to expand...at an accelerated rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.90,0:36:39.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量在宇宙最初的高温高密度的情况下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy is a constant term that was probably very insignificant...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.23,0:36:42.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是个微不足道的常数项\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the universe was hot and dense in the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.24,0:36:43.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以真的无关紧要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so it doesn't really matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.99,0:36:45.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不管暗能量是否存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether dark energy is there or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.45,0:36:48.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它存在 但根本就没有什么作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt is there, but it's... lt just plays no role at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.12,0:36:53.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然后随着宇宙变得越来越冷 密度越来越小 个头越来越大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, as the universe gets cooler and less dense and bigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.87,0:36:56.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以引力变得越来越重要\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so gravity becomes less important...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.75,0:36:58.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,于是暗能量有戏唱了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then dark energy takes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.71,0:37:03.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个空间特性我们尚未完全搞明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a property of space that we don't yet fully understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.59,0:37:08.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,随着宇宙的膨胀天文学家意识到暗能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the universe expanded, astronomers realized dark energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.10,0:37:09.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,赢得了与暗物质的斗争\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}won its struggle with dark matter...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.01,0:37:13.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在50亿年前开始了加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and started the acceleration five billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.89,0:37:17.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以有一段时间 约50亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there came a time, about five billion years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.86,0:37:23.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量开始主宰宇宙间的有吸引力的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the dark energy started dominating...over the attractive matter in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.69,0:37:27.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 在这里 如果你绘出力与时间矢量表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, in a sense, ifyou plot force versus time...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.24,0:37:29.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,万有引力一路下滑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gravitational attraction is declining with time...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.99,0:37:32.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,排斥力则一路攀升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the repulsion is increasing with time...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.54,0:37:36.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,约在50亿年前 两个曲线交汇了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and about five billion years ago, the two curves crossed...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.46,0:37:40.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就在那时 宇宙开始加速膨胀了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's when the universe started accelerating in its expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.17,0:37:44.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,暗能量是需要搞明白的关键\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Dark energy is fundamental to understand...
